)
```

In #1634, it was assumed that you cannot use the builder anymore after `await`ing it, which is why `.unwrap()` was used for `get_cache_settings`. However this isn't entirely correct because mutable references implement `Future` too, so this example would compile but panic at runtime:
```rs
let mut builder = Client::builder("a");

let client = (&mut builder).await.unwrap();

let settings = builder.get_cache_settings();
```
Instead of unwrapping, a note was added to the docs to reflect this. While this change isn't necessary for `http`, it avoids creating a new `Http` instance by using `std::mem::take()` that's most likely never even accessed anyway.

```
use std::fmt;

impl fmt::Display for T {
    fn fmt(&self, f: &mut fmt::Formatter<'_>) -> fmt::Result {
        // ...
    }
}

impl fmt::Debug for T {
    fn fmt(&self, f: &mut fmt::Formatter<'_>) -> fmt::Result {
        // ...
    }
}
```
